params.name: Path
params.doc: The path to the group. For more information about paths, see Identifiers for IAM Entities in Using AWS Identity and Access Management.  This parameter is optional. If it is not included, it defaults to a slash (/).

params.name: GroupName
params.doc: Name of the group to create. Do not include the path in this value.

properties.doc: Contains the result of a successful invocation of the CreateGroup action.
properties.name: CreateGroupResult
Path
properties.doc: Path to the group. For more information about paths, see Identifiers for IAM Entities in Using AWS Identity and Access Management.

properties.name: GroupName
properties.doc: The name that identifies the group.

properties.name: GroupId
properties.doc: The stable and unique string identifying the group. For more information about IDs, see Identifiers for IAM Entities in Using AWS Identity and Access Management.

properties.name: Arn
properties.doc: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) specifying the group. For more information about ARNs and how to use them in policies, see Identifiers for IAM Entities in Using AWS Identity and Access Management.
